{"questionId":"9510","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider the integral&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\int\\limits_1^t {\\frac{{ - 1}}{{x + {x^2}}}{\\text{ }}} dx\">\n  <munderover>\n    <mo>∫</mo>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mi>t</mi>\n  </munderover>\n  <mrow>\n    <mfrac>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>−</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <msup>\n            <mi>x</mi>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </msup>\n        </mrow>\n      </mrow>\n    </mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtext>&nbsp;</mtext>\n    </mrow>\n  </mrow>\n  <mi>d</mi>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span> for&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t > 1\">\n  <mi>t</mi>\n  <mo>&gt;</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Use parts (a) and (b) to show that <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{ln}}\\left( {1 + t} \\right) - {\\text{ln}}\\,t < {\\text{ln}}\\,2\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>ln</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mi>t</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>ln</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>t</mi>\n  <mo>&lt;</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>ln</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n</math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\int\\limits_1^t {\\frac{1}{{1 + x}} + \\frac{{ - 1}}{x}dx}&nbsp; = \\left[ {{\\text{ln}}\\left( {1 + x} \\right) - {\\text{ln}}\\,x} \\right]_1^t = {\\text{ln}}\\left( {1 + t} \\right) - {\\text{ln}}\\,t - {\\text{ln}}\\,2\">\n  <munderover>\n    <mo>∫</mo>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mi>t</mi>\n  </munderover>\n  <mrow>\n    <mfrac>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n      </mrow>\n    </mfrac>\n    <mo>+</mo>\n    <mfrac>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>−</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </mfrac>\n    <mi>d</mi>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <msubsup>\n    <mrow>\n      <mo>[</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <mtext>ln</mtext>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>(</mo>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n            <mo>+</mo>\n            <mi>x</mi>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>)</mo>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>−</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mtext>ln</mtext>\n        </mrow>\n        <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>]</mo>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mi>t</mi>\n  </msubsup>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>ln</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mi>t</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>ln</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>t</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>ln</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>Hence&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{ln}}\\left( {1 + t} \\right) - {\\text{ln}}\\,t - {\\text{ln}}\\,2 < 0 \\Rightarrow {\\text{ln}}\\left( {1 + t} \\right) - {\\text{ln}}\\,t < {\\text{ln}}\\,2\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>ln</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mi>t</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>ln</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>t</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>ln</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mo>&lt;</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇒</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>ln</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mi>t</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>ln</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>t</mi>\n  <mo>&lt;</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>ln</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>R1AG</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[4&nbsp;marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9510","referenceCode":"EXM.1.AHL.TZ0.2c","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Use parts (a) and (b) to show that ln ( 1 + t ) − ln t < ln 2 .","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.11—Partial fractions"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}